    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 1.84,
      "end": 4.04,
      "text": "This is a labor box recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 4.72,
      "end": 7.48,
      "text": "All labor box recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 8.36,
      "end": 12.94,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit laborbox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 13.8,
      "end": 17.32,
      "text": "Recorded by Patty McCoy in Hudson, Colorado.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 18.46,
      "end": 21.38,
      "text": "Aesop's Fables, the Faun and his mother.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.4,
      "end": 29.74,
      "text": "A hind said to her faun, who was now well grown and strong, my son nature has given",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 29.74,
      "end": 32.84,
      "text": "you a powerful body and a stout pair of horns.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 33.6,
      "end": 38.5,
      "text": "And I can't think why you are such a coward as to run away from the hounds.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 39.04,
      "end": 45.66,
      "text": "Just then they both heard the sound of a pack in full cry, but at a considerable distance.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 46.72,
      "end": 49.56,
      "text": "You stay where you are, said the hind.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 49.92,
      "end": 50.82,
      "text": "Never mind me.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 51.56,
      "end": 55.44,
      "text": "And with that, you ran off as fast as your legs could carry her.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 56.26,
      "end": 58.2,
      "text": "End of the faun and his mother.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
